Five persons have died in an accident on Keffi-Akwanaga Road at Aricha village of Akwanga local government area of Nasarawa State. The unit commander of the Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), Akwanaga, Ebere Onyegbado, confirmed the auto crash to LEADERSHIP, yesterday. He said that the multiple accidents involved a truck with registration number LSR 733 XX, a Sharon with registration number AE 165 GRU, a Hilux pickup with registration number GBE 16 EQ and a Toyota Hiace with registration number GBE 455 AE. Onyegbado said that the accident occurred on Friday afternoon at Aricha village at 2 pm, adding that one of the vehicles had lost control due to over speeding and had a head on collusion with the truck before others ran into it. According to him, 15 persons were involved in the accident, in which five people died, while 10 others sustained various degrees of injuries. The FRSC official said that the injured ones were immediately taken to OLA Hospital, Akwanga for treatment. Rev Dio Sallau Godwin, the senior pastor in charge of ECWA Church Number 4, Akwanga, was the driver of the Sharon car. Rev Dio died along with four members of the Women Fellowship of the Church in Akwanga. A source in the church said that they were returning to Akwanga from Gunduma in Keffi local government area where they went for burial.